# SeqWeb Tooling Rules

## CLI Structure
- Use modular command structure
- Keep commands focused and simple
- Provide clear help messages
- Support both short and long options
- Use consistent naming patterns
- Follow the `./seqweb` command pattern

## Development Tools
- Use Cursor as primary IDE
- Keep development environment clean and standardized
- Use Python virtual environments
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use type hints consistently
- Maintain polyglot development environment

## Testing
- Write unit tests for core functions
- Include integration tests for pipeline stages
- Test error conditions and edge cases
- Mock external services and dependencies
- Document test requirements
- Test cross-language module interactions

## Documentation
- Keep READMEs up to date
- Document all commands and tools
- Include usage examples
- Maintain changelog
- Use clear, direct language
- Document diagram workflows and maintenance

## Version Control
- Use mainline development
- Make focused commits
- Write clear commit messages
- Keep history clean
- Push changes regularly
- Use "git consolidate" for rapid commits

## Diagram Management
- Use Draw.io for diagram creation
- Export SVGs manually as best practice
- Keep .drawio and .svg files together
- Use check_diagrams.py for maintenance
- Embed SVGs in documentation consistently
